parameters:
\n<Sister>Oh...! You with the cat ears...! You must be new here! Are
you here to join our faith? To join us!?

\n<Sister>Ah, you're not here to join. Well, I'm just happy that
someone came to visit Nice to meet you. I'm Soel, a sister
of the Storm Church.
\n<Sister>You're \n[1]-san, right? It's a pleasure to meet you.

\n<Sister>There aren't many devout people here, and few come to
worship, so rather than a sister, it might be more
appropriate to call me a gravekeeper...

\n<Sister>Please come to this church anytime If you'd like, I would
also be happy to talk to you about our doctrine.
C

\n<Sister>This is the church where we pass on the teachings of one of
the four sages, Storm-sama. It seems you too are blessed by
the wind. Even if not all, perhaps half of it will resonate
with your heart.

\n<Sister>That someone like you has drifted into this town... I
understand there must have been very difficult and complex
circumstances. Please allow me to at least pray for your
peace.

\n<Sister>The human heart cannot always be pure. Anger, sadness,
jealousy, hatred... unbearable emotions may arise at times.

\n<Sister>Sometimes, it's important to let things be as they are.
After a storm rages, there must be a quiet and clear world
that can only be seen then.

\n<Sister>The people of fire are passionate, and the people of wind
loved freedom. The spark within you will someday be fanned
into a great flame by the wind. You have good attributes.

\n<Sister>I do not like to use the term "lower class," but it was said
that "even those from the lower ranks need prayers," and
thus this church was built.

\n<Sister>This church is sustained by donations from above. Mercy
should be extended to all people.

\n<Sister>This place is a church, but at the same time, it is also a
graveyard. If anything, its role as a graveyard might be
stronger since, unfortunately, there aren't many devout
believers.

\n<Sister>But still... what do you call it... these cat ears... they
make you want to touch them, don't they?
\n<Sister>Hehe... How cute.
\n<Sister>Now, let us pray together...! Come! Come!

\n<Sister>What to consider a sin, and what to punish. Providing
standards to uphold and keeping from straying from the path.
That is the "teaching."
\n<Sister>...
\n<Sister>...
\n<Sister>Zzz... Zzz...
\n<Sister>...! Nngh...
\n<Sister>I wasn't sleeping, I wasn't sleeping. I was praying.

\n<Soel>This is the church where we preach the teachings of one of
the Four Sages, Storm-sama. It seems you too are blessed by
the wind. Even if not all, perhaps half of it will resonate
with your heart.

\n<Soel>It seems you've come to understand my thoughts a little
Teehee

\n<Soel>What brings you here? If there's something you wish to
"confess," please head to the confessional

\n<Soel>The human heart cannot always be pure. Anger, sadness,
jealousy, hatred... Overwhelming emotions may arise.

\n<Soel>Sometimes, it's important to let things out as they are.
After a storm rages, there must be a quiet and clear world
that can only be seen then.
\n<Soel>\n[1]-san What's the matter? Did you come to see me? Fufu
\n<Soel>Ahh My stomach... it kicked...

\n<Soel>Just kidding It's a joke, a joke It can't grow that fast,
can it? Teehee

\n<Soel>I don't like the term "lower class," but this church was
built on the idea that "even those from the lower echelons
need prayer."

\n<Soel>This is a true story. I've just utilized it a bit for my
hobby, but there's no mistake that I am a real sister.

\n<Soel>This place is a church, but at the same time, it's also a
graveyard. If anything, its role as a graveyard might be
stronger since, unfortunately, there aren't many devout
believers.

\n<Soel>Thanks to that, my research is progressing well. It keeps
the town clean too, killing two birds with one stone

\n<Soel>But really... cat ears... what do you call them... I just
want to touch them.

\n<Soel>Hehe... They're cute. Later on, I might give them even more
love

\n<Soel>Hey \n[1]-san Would you mind making a donation? A
donation

\n<Soel>If you donate, I'll listen to lots of confessions for you
Teehee

\n<Soel>What to consider as sin, and what to punish. Providing
standards to abide by and keeping one from straying off the
path. That is the "teaching."

\n<Soel>Storm-sama had a realistic point of view. I'm just acting
according to those teachings. Sometimes, that means stepping
outside of ethics.
\n<Soel>...
\n<Soel>...
\n<Soel>Zzz... Zzz...
\n<Soel>...! Nnh...

\n<Soel>What is it? I'm sleep-deprived from experiments. It's fine
to sleep a little, isn't it...
\n<Sister>Yes, how may I assist you?...

\n<Sister>This person in the portrait... Yes, I remember. They passed
away from an illness...

\n<Sister>You saw this person walking around...? Oh no, please don't
tell such a scary story.

\n<Sister>It might have been someone who looks similar. Hmm... I can't
think of anyone...

\n<Sister>You want to investigate around the church? Yes, of course,
that's fine. There are no services today, so...

\n<Sister>Please feel free to look around. And if you encounter any
ghosts, please save me
B

\n<Sister>I feel so happy when \n[1]-san comes to visit Even if it's
just for work Nfufu

I love the piano. Someday, I want to play a duet using cat's
cradle.

Stained glass that seems out of place in the slums. I feel
reluctant to break such a grand window.

The stained glass feels out of place in the slums. I feel
resistant to breaking such a fine window.

\n<Suspicious Man>"This town doesn't suit such a grand church, does it? Seems
like it was built with the money from those higher-ups. If
they have that kind of money, they should be handing out
food instead, damn hypocrites."

\n<Suspicious Man>"Oops, maybe I'll be punished for saying such things... If
faith could fill one's stomach, I'd pray for a lifetime."

\n<Suspicious Man>"With the sister gone, this church is finished, huh? Or will
someone else come to take her place, I wonder?"

\n<Suspicious Man>"Necromancy or whatever is fine, but just make sure to clean
up the corpses properly. They're the most troublesome kind
of trash after all."

\n<Suspicious Man>"I may think faith can go to hell, but graveyards do serve a
purpose. Maybe I'll make a donation once in a while."

\n<Believer?>By offering prayers, you can gradually remove the black mold
that spreads in your heart. Now, you too should pray.

\n<\n[1]>(While making a gesture of prayer, they're slightly opening
their eyes looking for something. It seems like they're
casing the place for something to steal...)

\n<Believer?>"I knew it was suspicious. Such a grand church like this...
Let's steal what we can while we still have the chance."

\n<Believer?>"I thought I might find something to steal passing by, but I
was truly touched by the Sister's earnestness. Who the hell
started that awful rumor, seriously? What a scumbag."

\n<Follower>At first, I didn't think we needed a church, but having
someone to perform services for the dead and manage the
cemetery is a relief. If bodies are left as they are, they
can spread disease.

\n<Follower>And the sister is such a good person. She listens to our
troubles with compassion, she's gentle and pure-hearted.
Talking to her feels like it cleanses your own soul.

\n<Follower>I still can't believe that Soel-san was tampering with a
corpse. Could there have been a reason for it?

\n<Follower>No, even if there was a reason, it's not acceptable. Perhaps
her mind was already broken when she came here.

\n<Follower>Even though you've been tending to the graves, to be accused
of necromancy... It's a cruel rumor that's been spread, poor
Sister. Who could do such a thing...
\n<\n[1]>(It's me! It's me! It's not a rumor... Ugh...)

\n<\n[1]>(A rumor, huh... Maybe it was better this way for these
people...)

\n<Believer?>Soel-chan is amazing, isn't she? She has the air of a pure
lady, yet those breasts are something else. It's no wonder
people come to pray.
\n<Believer?>Makes you want to offer something up, right?
\n<\n[1]>Offer what?

\n<Believer?>Huh? Where's Soel-chan? Hey, I came to see Soel-chan. Do you
know where they went? Do they have a day off or something?

\n<Believer?>Poor Soel-chan, it's sad how weird rumors are being spread
about her. I don't know if they're true or not, but hey, you
can mess with my corpse as much as you want. Hehe
\n<\n[1]>Gross! (You can keep my dead body by your side...)

\n<\n[1]>(Even if he knew her true identity, it seems like this
person wouldn't care...)

\n<Follower>I'm of the thunder and water elements, so there's no church
for me. Hey, little one, you're of fire and wind, aren't
you? You must have your own struggles too.

\n<Follower>Well, elements and such aren't the essence of a person. It's
all about experiences rather than birth. "It's how you
live," my grandpa always said. He's dead now, though.

\n<Believer>The sister's been captured. Well, I've also lost my old man
and wished countless times for him to come back to life.

\n<Believer>Those obsessed with necromancy must have someone they
desperately wanted to bring back to life, I suppose. But I
don't know.

\n<Follower>Someone's been spreading nasty rumors about the Sister using
necromancy. Just look into those sparkling eyes.

\n<Follower>Ah, the very picture of innocence. You can tell when you've
lived as long as I have. She's not a bad kid.
\n<\n[1]>(You're not seeing clearly, granny...)

\n<\n[1]>(Even with age, there are things you just don't
understand...)
Let's investigate a little more.

It's the door to the confessional. What is there to
confess...

Where should I start apologizing from... Maybe from
grandpa's vase, huh.
